ght/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aThis anthology offers the first comprehensive overview of media hype, a phenomenon often dismissed as ephemeral and unimportant. Despite that reputation, media storms actually do play an important role in political issues, scandals, and crises, sometimes creating an important shift in public opinion over the course of only a few hours. This book provides an overview of theoretical, conceptual, and methodological issues related to media hype through close explorations of case studies from around the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aDigital media. 0aOnline journalism. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aMedia Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aNews waves, media hype, twitter storms, public opinion, social problems.1 aAtteveldt, Wouter van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAuch, Adam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeyer, Audun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrin, Colette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarlsson, Pernille, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCerase, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChung, Ik Jae, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElmelund-Præstekær, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFigenschou, Tine Ustad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeiß, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiass